<tr><td bgcolor="#3F403F" width="98%" class="cheader"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php3'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></td><td bgcolor="3F403F" valign="top" align="right" width="22"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/topcorner.gif" width="23" height="22" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0" align="right"></td></tr>
<tr><td width="98%" colspan=2><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" class="cbody">
<tr><td><font class="h1font"> Brian Hollingworth - Player Created V9 Card<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=175'>Scott "CRingwell" Lingrell</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=175&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> April 21, 2005</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Entrenchment (v)<br />
Effect<br />
Deploy on table. Whenever opponent Force drains, if you control two battlegrounds (a site and a system), or Jedi Test 1 on table, you may choose to lose Force equal to the number of Light Side icons at that location instead of losing Force to the Force drain. (Immune to Alter.)<br />
<br />
	I’ll start with why I wanted to make this card.  Ever since before Tatooine came out, QMC has been my favorite deck to play. It was good for a while, but now it just can’t keep up with decks like Walkers or Maul that can set up huge, un-cancelable, un-modifiable drains very quickly.  I didn’t just want to make a QMC helper though, because it already has a couple and I also wanted to make a card that could work in many different decks, not just QMC.<br />
<br />
	I decided to sit down and think of why defensive decks like QMC are no longer competitive.  I came up with three main reasons why they can’t compete anymore:<br />
1) Aforementioned huge drains that can’t be touched let the DS completely ignore the LS player and cause far more damage far faster than the LS player can hope to cause.<br />
2) DS space is so incredibly strong right now it is very hard for the LS player to hold a system, which is imperative for the LS to do.<br />
3) Scum is very good and is inherently good against a deck that puts characters at sites.<br />
<br />
	I knew I couldn’t address all of these problems with one card, so I had to choose one to do.  I chose to address problem number 1 because it is the only problem that can be completely removed with a single card.  While DS space being very strong and potentially denying the LS player the system required for Entrenchment (v) is a big deal, with enough planning and deck building designed to hold a system it can be done, whereas if I made a card designed to help LS space QMC would still be unplayable due to the drains.  As for the scum problem, it is a major problem, and it is unlikely that QMC will be playable again until scum decreases in popularity, but since scum is so incredibly strong, I expect we will see some toning down of it in the next couple of sets.<br />
<br />
	Having decided which problem to address, I needed to work out exactly how to do it.  Back when QMC originated and for a long time after it’s strength was in being able to set up battle plan / menace fades and celebration to limit the damage it took while slowly eating away at the opponents life force.  In the current game, this is impossible as menace fades has been essentially neutered by cards like Bane Malor (v), rodian (v), Despair (v), Imperial Occupation (v), ect.  I needed to make a card that could get around these cards but not destroy their decktypes.  Originally I made a defensive shield that said the LS player could ignore any text preventing force drains and bonuses from being canceled, but the PC didn’t want any more defensive shields, and it just turned out that the wording of the card (canceling un-cancelable things) was too confusing and had the potential to lead to problems.  I drew a blank for a little while as to what to do next, then when my playtesting group got a new list of V9 cards to playtest, there was a card in the set much like mine, that allowed the LS player to retrieve force equal to the bonus the opponent just drained for.  While I didn’t particularly like this card, because it only worked once per turn and I didn’t like the retrieving aspect, it did give me the idea that the card didn’t have to affect the bonuses themselves, just the force that is lost.  Thus, this card was born.	<br />
	While I designed this card with QMC in mind, it can certainly be used in other decks as well.  WYS comes to mind immediately, as well as just about any Careful Planning (v) start.<br />
<br />
Here’s a deck I made to make use of Entrenchment (v), and since I made it to help QMC it is of course a QMC deck.<br />
<br />
Thrown Back (v)  w/ shields<br />
QMC<br />
Bespin<br />
Guest Quarters<br />
Keeping the Empire Out Forever<br />
