Entrenchment (v)<br />
<br />
X-Wing Laser Cannon<br />
Intruder Missile x2<br />
<br />
I&#39;ll Take the Leader<br />
<br />
<br />
This deck plays like any other QMC, set up in space then go to ground with evasion.  The most important thing here is not to try and flip too fast.  Never go to space until you can get at least two ships up there, because if you play just Dash he will die immediately.  The first couple of turns should be spent fortifying space, then drop a couple of guys on the ground to flip.  After that just celebrate, drain, and battle the opponent off CC.<br />
<br />
Some card choices and things people might not know:<br />
Ten Numb – he’s a monster in blue 5 with missiles, adds +4 to total weapon destiny for anything fired so he’ll take out the cruiser, Bossk in ship, random star destroyers, and even the Executor with 2 shots and tracking.<br />
No Civil (v) – barrier is just too good not to play.  It barriers Fett who is the biggest threat to space, it barriers ships that react with the cruiser which is huge, and it prevents the opponent from battling altogether at sites sometimes, which is much better than evasion because you’re opponent doesn’t get to retrieve for battling.<br />
Sorry about the mess – better destiny than the combo, and is always used in control phase anyways so celebration can retrieve it.  Remember that this works in space too, so taking out the cruiser in the control phase can be game winning.<br />
Honor – firepower (v) hurts this deck bad.  Honor stops it (remember defensive shields are not protected by no escape).<br />
